The term '''Latin America and the Caribbean''' ('''LAC''')<ref>http://www.unesco.org/new/en/unesco/worldwide/latin-america-and-the-caribbean/</ref> is an [[English language|English-language]] [[acronym]] referring to the [[Caribbean]] and [[Latin America]] region. The term LAC covers an extensive region, extending from [[Bahamas]] to [[Chile]] and [[Argentina]]. The region consists over 670.230.000 people as for 2016, and spanned for 21.951.000 km<sup>2</sup> (8.475.000 sq mi).

