{{Italic title}}
'''''The Good Gardens Guide''''' (sometimes subtitled "The Essential Independent Guide to the 1200 Best Gardens, Parks and Green Spaces in Britain, Ireland and the Channel Islands") is a guide to the best gardens in the [[British Isles]], published annually. Some of the gardens featured are not usually open to the public, and are only open by prior appointment with the owner.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.emeraldinsight.com/journals.htm?issn=0950-4125&volume=17&issue=6&articleid=1497214&show=html&PHPSESSID=lvgupodkuggjgtccn7u2chbcl1 | title=(Review): The Good Gardens Guide 2003 (14th edition) | publisher=Reference Reviews | work=Vol. 17, Issue 6 | year=2003 | accessdate=July 6, 2012 | author=Thurlow, Jane | pages=51–52}}</ref>

Gardener and garden writer [[Alan Titchmarsh]] endorsed the book, stating "I never go anywhere without it."<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gardening/3315314/Gardening-email.html | title=The Daily Telegraph Good Gardens Guide | publisher=''The Telegraph'' | date=November 6, 2003 | accessdate=July 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>''The Good Gardens Guide'' front cover</ref>

